msContents.summary: Medical Manual. The manuscript contains 17 magic formulae, of which 16 are contemporary, while one is written in a later hand from the seventeenth century.

msItem.title: Medical Manual
msItem.textLang: Most of the headings are in Latin; the rest of the text is in Old Danish
msItem.rubric:
Iæk hygger thær vm at manghæ takær til
at wære lækæ thæn thær æy kan forthi ha
uer iæk leet sæn lækædom. oc hanum hauer iæk
skreuet
msItem.incipit:
Hær byries af howæth wærk. hu
Hwat thær scal gøres fore Tac osæn af
swartæ beto. oc lat mæth halft af hunægh
oc lat thæt i næsæ. thøm thær houeth wærk
hauer
msItem.explicit:
For ict siuth æspæ barc i. got øll. oc
dric een skal warmt thær af arlæ om mor

msItem.locus: The lower margin of fol. 16v contains a magic formula in six lines, written in cursive
msItem.title: A Magic Formula
msItem.incipit: Vor herre Jesus bleff saaret i Jorderig
msItem.explicit:
Saa skal oc icke dette helder gióre
j naffn Gud faders Söns oc Helligand.

msItem.title: Household remedies
msItem.incipit:
Tag en god handfuld mett holfwrtt rod oc skeer
hendæ i smaa stycker
msItem.explicit:
oc

foliation.p: There is a younger foliation on fols 1-56 in the upper right-hand corner of the recto pages, and on fols 57-59 below the text, probably by Kristian Kålund.

collation.p: It seems that fol. 59 was originally pasted towards the lower board of the binding as traces of glue are found on it. There are catchwords on fols 10v, 18v, 26v, 36v and 52v.

condition.p: Three leaves have been excised between fols 28 and 29, 35 and 36, and 56 and 57.

layout.p: The manuscript is written in long lines with 25 lines per page. The first letter of each main part of the book consists of a blue initial occupying 2 to 4 lines. Each paragraph begins with a red majuscule. The headings are either red or underlined in red.

handNote.p: The main hand written in a fourteenth-century gothic bookhand occupies fols 1r-56v (the medical manual).
The magic formula on fol. 16v is written in a seventeenth-century younger gothic cursive.

additions.p: Younger marginalia occur here and there. A number of pen trials can be found on fol. 57r.

binding.p:
The binding consists of wooden boards covered with pigskin, originally tanned red, now faded to a brownish colour. A lock mechanism and the strap are missing, but the heart-shaped brass plate to fasten the strap is still on the front cover. When Kristian Kålund catalogued the manuscript in 1888, the back was padded with small pieces of parchment, covered with writing and which were subsequently removed. One of these fragments was transferred to Accessoria 7 where it is catalogued as Acc. 7c, hs 141. The dimensions of the binding are:
167 131 41 .

accMat.p:
There is an AM-slip written by Árni Magnússon pasted to fol. 1r which reads: num. 1038. ex
auctione Rostgard..

origin.p:
The medical manual was written in Denmark. Three datings for the manuscript have been put forward:
Kristian Kålund: the fourteenth century ( Katalog II 437 )
Viggo Såby: the second half of the fourteenth century ( Det Arnamagnæanske håndskrift nr 187, 8vo iii )
Erik Kroman: the beginning of the fifteenth century ( Dansk Palæografi 68 )

provenance.p:
The name Hans Hansen appears on fol. 57r, and on fol. 1r
Christianus Bordingius
M.D. apud Ripens. Ordin. claims ownership of the book. Later Frederik Rostgaard has owned the book.

acquisition.p: According to the AM-slip, Árni Magnússon purchased the book at the Rostgaard auction in 1729.

source.p: Catalogued 15 September 1999 by AMH, AWS and EW-J

custEvent.p: The manuscript was photographed for the first time in 1960 (before restoration).

Portraits of the binding: upper board, lower board and spine, end-papers, openings of the book: 10v-11r, 52v-53r and a close-up of the clasp were taken 30 March 1998 before lending the manuscript to an exhibition.
Coloured diapositives were taken of the following folios 2 April 1998: 1r, 6v-7r, 16v-17r, 27v-28r, 30v-31r, 53v-54r, 54v-55r.

The manuscript has been lent to The Danish National Archives (Rigsarkivet), Copenhagen, on four occasions for the use of Erik Kroman: from 3 to 17 April 1959; from 20 to 24 April 1961; from 23 to 25 March 1963, and from 7 to 27 April 1965.
The manuscript was lent to Dansk Folkemindesamling, Copenhagen for the use of Jørn Piø on 10 November 1961.
The manuscript was exhibited twice in Esrum Kloster in North Sjælland. The first time in May-August 1998 and the second time 8 to 26 October 1998.
